  "architecture_summary": "Multiscale Vision Transformers (MViT) connect multiscale feature hierarchies with transformer models by using several channel-resolution scale stages that hierarchically expand channel capacity while reducing spatial resolution. The model uses Multi Head Pooling Attention (MHPA) and MLP layers to build a multiscale pyramid of features for video and image recognition.",
